## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="c7b83-102">System.Speech 위한 기본 의미 형식 W3C에 맞는 [음성 인식 (SISR) 버전 1.0에 대 한 의미 해석](http://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/?LinkId=201765)여기서에 대 한 형식 `tag` 스크립트를 포함 하는 요소는 `semantics/1.0`합니다.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="c7b83-102">The default semantic format for System.Speech conforms to the W3C [Semantic Interpretation for Speech Recognition (SISR) Version 1.0](http://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/?LinkId=201765), where the format for `tag` elements that contain script is `semantics/1.0`.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="c7b83-103">에 대 한 스크립트를 지정 해야 <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsSemanticInterpretationTag> 이 형식을 사용 하 여 개체입니다.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="c7b83-103">You must specify the script for <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsSemanticInterpretationTag> objects using this format.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="c7b83-104">구문에서 `semantics/1.0`:</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="c7b83-104">In the syntax of `semantics/1.0`:</span></span>  
  
-   <span data-ttu-id="c7b83-105">포함 규칙 요소의 규칙 변수 "out"으로 식별 됩니다.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="c7b83-105">The Rule Variable of the containing rule element is identified by "out".</span></span>  
  
-   <span data-ttu-id="c7b83-106">규칙 변수 규칙 요소는 포함 하는 규칙 요소 외부에 액세스할 수 있는 개체의 이름은 "규칙"으로 식별 됩니다.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="c7b83-106">The name of the object that has access to the Rule Variable of rule elements outside the containing rule element is identified by "rules".</span></span>  
  
-   <span data-ttu-id="c7b83-107">최신 참조 된 규칙의 utterance 일치 하는 결과 "rules.latest()"로 나타낼 수 있습니다.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="c7b83-107">The result from the latest referenced rule that matches the utterance can be represented by "rules.latest()".</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="c7b83-108">스크립트를 사용 하지 않고 문법에 구문으로 의미 체계는 값을 연결할 수도 있습니다를 사용 하 여 <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsNameValueTag> 개체입니다.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="c7b83-108">You can also associate a semantic value with a phrase in a grammar without using script, using the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsNameValueTag> object.</span></span>  
  
   
  
## Examples  
 <span data-ttu-id="c7b83-109">다음 예제는 항공편에 대 한 도시를 선택 하기 위한 문법을 만듭니다.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="c7b83-109">The following example creates a grammar for choosing the cities for a flight.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="c7b83-110">이 예제에서는 사용 <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsSemanticInterpretationTag> 공항 도시에 대 한 코드의 각 도시를 의미 체계 값을 할당 하 합니다.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="c7b83-110">The example uses <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsSemanticInterpretationTag> to assign a semantic value to each city, which is the code for the city's airport.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="c7b83-111">또한이 예제에서는 <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsSemanticInterpretationTag> 각 수행한 두 참조에 대해 별도 의미 체계 키를 할당 하는 <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRuleRef> 라는 개체 `cityRef` 에 <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRule> 라는 개체 `cities`합니다.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="c7b83-111">The example also uses <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsSemanticInterpretationTag> to assign a separate semantic key for each of the two references made by the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRuleRef> object named `cityRef` to the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRule> object named `cities`.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="c7b83-112">의미 체계 키 출발 도시 또는 항공권 도착 시 인식할된 도시를 식별합니다.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="c7b83-112">The semantic keys identify a recognized city as the departure city or the arrival city for the flight.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="c7b83-113">에 대 한 처리기는 <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognitionEngine.SpeechRecognized> 이벤트 키를 사용 하 여 인식 결과에서 의미 체계를 검색 합니다.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="c7b83-113">The handler for the <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SpeechRecognitionEngine.SpeechRecognized> event uses the keys to retrieve the semantics from the recognition result.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="c7b83-114">코드 예제 "out"는 포함 하는 규칙 변수를 참조 <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRule>합니다.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="c7b83-114">In the code example, "out" refers to the Rule Variable of the containing <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRule>.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="c7b83-115">식 "아웃 했습니다. LeavingFrom"라는 속성이 가리킵니다 `LeavingFrom` 이라는 규칙에서 규칙 변수의 `bookFlight`합니다.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="c7b83-115">The expression "out.LeavingFrom" refers to the property named `LeavingFrom` of the Rule Variable on the rule named `bookFlight`.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="c7b83-116">식 "rules.flightCities"를 참조 하는 규칙에서 규칙 변수 갖는 <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRule.Id%2A> 은 `flightCities`, 규칙 참조의 대상이 됩니다.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="c7b83-116">The expression "rules.flightCities" refers to the Rule Variable on the rule whose <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRule.Id%2A> is `flightCities`, and which is the target of a rule reference.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="c7b83-117">예제에서는 식 "제한입니다. LeavingFrom=rules.flightCities;"규칙에서 값을 할당 인 <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRule.Id%2A> 은 `flightCities` 라는 속성을 `LeavingFrom` 이라는 규칙에서 규칙 변수의 `bookFlight`합니다.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="c7b83-117">In the example, the expression "out.LeavingFrom=rules.flightCities;" assigns the value from the rule whose <xref:System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar.SrgsRule.Id%2A> is `flightCities` to the property named `LeavingFrom` of the Rule Variable on the rule named `bookFlight`.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="c7b83-118">참조 [의미 체계 결과 콘텐츠](http://msdn.microsoft.com/library/622291af-615c-4a15-9014-2933aa3f89fe), [문법 규칙 이름을 참조 하](http://msdn.microsoft.com/library/0777e975-8665-4cc3-957b-752743cb1bb9), 및 [문법 규칙 참조 참조](http://msdn.microsoft.com/library/dec3a809-9aa2-4139-893f-3a549ca1e03e) 자세한 정보에 대 한 합니다.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="c7b83-118">See [Semantic Results Content](http://msdn.microsoft.com/library/622291af-615c-4a15-9014-2933aa3f89fe), [Grammar Rule Name Referencing](http://msdn.microsoft.com/library/0777e975-8665-4cc3-957b-752743cb1bb9), and [Grammar Rule Reference Referencing](http://msdn.microsoft.com/library/dec3a809-9aa2-4139-893f-3a549ca1e03e) for more information.</span></span>  
  
```  
using System;  
using System.Speech.Recognition;  
using System.Speech.Recognition.SrgsGrammar;  
  
namespace SampleRecognition  
{  
  class Program  
  {  
    static void Main(string[] args)  
  
    // Initialize a SpeechRecognitionEngine object.  
    {  
      using (SpeechRecognitionEngine recognizer =  
         new SpeechRecognitionEngine(new System.Globalization.CultureInfo("en-US")))  
      {  
  
        // Create a rule for the cities, assign a semantic value to each city.  
        SrgsRule cities = new SrgsRule("flightCities");  
        SrgsItem chi = new SrgsItem("Chicago");  
        chi.Add(new SrgsSemanticInterpretationTag("out = \"ORD\";"));  
        SrgsItem bos = new SrgsItem("Boston");  
        bos.Add(new SrgsSemanticInterpretationTag("out = \"BOS\";"));  
        SrgsItem mia = new SrgsItem("Miami");  
        mia.Add(new SrgsSemanticInterpretationTag("out = \"MIA\";"));  
        SrgsItem dal = new SrgsItem("Dallas");  
        dal.Add(new SrgsSemanticInterpretationTag("out = \"DFW\";"));  
  
        SrgsOneOf airports = new SrgsOneOf(chi, bos, mia, dal);  
        cities.Add(airports);  
        cities.Scope = SrgsRuleScope.Private;  
  
        // Create a rule reference to the rule for cities.  
        SrgsRuleRef cityRef = new SrgsRuleRef(cities);  
  
        // Create the root rule for the grammar.  
        SrgsRule bookFlight = new SrgsRule("flightBooker");  
        bookFlight.Add(new SrgsItem("I want to fly from"));  
        bookFlight.Add(cityRef);  
        bookFlight.Add(new SrgsSemanticInterpretationTag("out.LeavingFrom=rules.flightCities;"));  
        bookFlight.Add(new SrgsItem("to"));  
        bookFlight.Add(cityRef);  
        bookFlight.Add(new SrgsSemanticInterpretationTag("out.GoingTo=rules.flightCities;"));  
        bookFlight.Scope = SrgsRuleScope.Public;  
  
        // Initialize the SrgsDocument, set the root rule, add rules to the collection.  
        SrgsDocument itinerary = new SrgsDocument(bookFlight);  
        itinerary.Rules.Add(cities);  
  
        // Create a Grammar object and load it to the recognizer.  
        Grammar g = new Grammar(itinerary);  
        g.Name = ("City Chooser");  
        recognizer.LoadGrammarAsync(g);  
  
        // Configure recognizer input.                  
        recognizer.SetInputToDefaultAudioDevice();  
  
        // Attach a handler for the SpeechRecognized event.  
        recognizer.SpeechRecognized +=  
          new EventHandler<SpeechRecognizedEventArgs>(recognizer_SpeechRecognized);  
  
        // Start recognition.  
        recognizer.RecognizeAsync();  
        Console.WriteLine("Starting asynchronous recognition...");  
  
        // Keep the console window open.  
        Console.ReadLine();  
      }  
    }  
  
    // Write to the console the text and the semantics from the recognition result.  
    static void recognizer_SpeechRecognized(object sender, SpeechRecognizedEventArgs e)  
    {  
      Console.WriteLine("Speech recognized: " + e.Result.Text);  
      Console.WriteLine();  
      Console.WriteLine("Semantic results:");  
      Console.WriteLine("  The departure city is: " + e.Result.Semantics["LeavingFrom"].Value);  
      Console.WriteLine("  The arrival city is: " + e.Result.Semantics["GoingTo"].Value);  
    }  
  }  
}  
  
```  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="c7b83-119">다음은 위의 예제에서 코드에 의해 생성 된 문법의 XML 형식입니다.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="c7b83-119">The following is the XML form of the grammar generated by the code in the example above.</span></span>  
  
```xml  
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>  
<grammar xml:lang="en-US" root="flightBooker" tag-format="semantics/1.0"   
version="1.0" xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2001/06/grammar">  
  
  <rule id="flightBooker" scope="public">  
    <item> I want to fly from </item>  
    <ruleref uri="#flightCities" />   
    <tag> out.LeavingFrom=rules.flightCities; </tag>  
    <item> to </item>  
    <ruleref uri="#flightCities" />   
    <tag> out.GoingTo=rules.flightCities; </tag>  
  </rule>  
  
  <rule id="flightCities" scope="private">  
    <one-of>  
      <item> Chicago <tag> out="ORD"; </tag></item>  
      <item> Boston <tag> out="BOS"; </tag></item>  
      <item> Miami <tag> out="MIA"; </tag></item>  
      <item> Dallas <tag> out="DFW"; </tag></item>  
    </one-of>  
  </rule>  
  
</grammar>  
```
